# 🧠 Ratne ka Tarika (Memory Tricks)

### 🪄 Trick 1:

> **“Strategy = Replace if-else with classes”**

---

### 🪄 Trick 2:

> **“Same kaam + multiple ways = Strategy Pattern”**

Examples:

* Payment → UPI / Card / Netbanking
* Navigation → Car / Bike / Walking
* Notification → Email / SMS / WhatsApp

---

### 🪄 Trick 3 (Interview line):

> **“Encapsulate varying behavior and make it interchangeable at runtime”**

---

### 🪄 Trick 4 (1-liner story):

> “Client decides WHAT, Strategy decides HOW”

---

# 🧭 When to Use Strategy Pattern?

Use when:

### ✅ 1. Multiple ways to perform same task

* Example: Payment methods

### ✅ 2. Too many if-else

* Replace with polymorphism

### ✅ 3. Need runtime flexibility

* Change behavior dynamically

### ✅ 4. Want to follow SOLID principles

---

# ⚠️ When NOT to Use

❌ Only one logic exists
❌ No variation in behavior
❌ Over-engineering small problems

---

# 🆚 Strategy vs Command (Important)

| Feature | Strategy                       | Command                |
| ------- | ------------------------------ | ---------------------- |
| Purpose | Different ways to do same task | Encapsulate request    |
| Focus   | Algorithm                      | Action                 |
| Example | Payment methods                | Remote control buttons |

---

# 🔥 Interview पहचान (Recognition Tip)

If interviewer says:

👉 “Add new feature without modifying existing code”
👉 “Multiple ways to do same thing”
👉 “Remove if-else”

➡️ तुरंत बोलो:

> **“We can use Strategy Pattern here”**

---

# 💡 Final Summary

* Create **interface (strategy)**
* Create **multiple implementations**
* Pass strategy via **constructor**
* Call method → **dynamic behavior**

